reviews.text: Located underground but not hard to find. Beef portion was small but tasty. Great fried chicken and honey sauce. Cheese corn is always delicious and all-you-can-eat. Bae and Henry loved it! Good value for money.

Great value of a lunch set that changes pretty regularly. Love how they are quite generous with the portions. The taste is decent if not spectacular comparing to the more authentic joints in the neighborhood. Overall not bad for an easy weekday lunch break kind of place, would come back and try the barbeque at some point.
Awesome place for its price especially with promotion. Food is super good

After 3 years, still our favorite place for a dinner..
Super friendly staff helping us to grill and explain the step..
Surprising good, I actually visited here for the second time. It is better than the bigger brands in Hong Kong.

result.name: MeokBang Korean BBQ

reviews.text:
Nice Korean bbq restaurant, the food quality is pretty good and price is fair.  Service is good as well.  The waitress will remind you not to overcook the meat.  Good for gathering and they serve beer tower too!   

The dessert might run out so if you want to try specific dessert, remember to reserve it at the beginning of your meal!

Firstly,the servers don't even know english.
Secondly, their food wasn't Korean quality- i have literally tried every Korean food in hk and this place was my least favourite place .Literally, where do i even start, their meat was badly frozen, their sweet chicken was so sticky i couldn’t t even chew it, the Kimchi Fried Rice was the only thing nice but had no salt and lacked that authentic Korean flavour. Lastly, when i asked just for the pork set the servers literally forced me to select another meat set saying both meat set was included on the same price as pork set. And at the end they charged me for both meat set like seriously. I don’t recommend this restaurant to anyone.
It tastes better than the same franchise nearby, but it can improve its hygiene a bit more
Happy New ki ok
Fun bbq place with friends. Advance booking is suggested.
